"    Fat content of oils",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 472px; height: 341px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    When fats are needed for cooking, spreads, and other uses, oils with higher amounts of monounsaturated and/or polyunsaturated fatty acids should be used,&nbsp;such as canola oil and olive oil. Those oils that are higher in&nbsp;n-3 polyunsaturated fats (alpha-linoleic acid, ALA)&nbsp;such as walnut oil and, to a lesser extent, soybean oil are also beneficial. Linoleic acid (LA) is an n-6 polyunsaturated fatty acid.",
